<br>
Ragefire Camp list and rule. <br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
The following rules were established by the first 10 clerics on the original list. It is up to each cleric that holds the list, to add, take away, or revise the rules as they see fit, BUT they need the approval of the first 10 ppl on the list to make any changes. This email is to be updated and distributed to each of the clerics on the list, however, we do not have all the email addresses. So, please do your part to help collect the email addresses when you are the list holder.<br>
<br>
The rules are as follows:<br>
<br>
1. The only person that can add to the list of campers, is the person camping. In order to be added to the list, you must contact the person camping, not any of the other clerics. Before being added to the list, the person that wants to be added, must agree to a few things.<br>
<br>
2. They should be online or available as much as possible for the person before them on the list. Both of these clerics should be in Skyfire, and &quot;holding the camp&quot;. Holding the camp serves two purposes, 1- keeping other people from KS'ing or trying to; and 2-keeping someone online in <br>
skyfire in case Ragefire spawns.<br>
<br>
3. In order to be added to the list, they must agree to maintain the list when it is their turn at Ragefire.<br>
<br>
4. They agree to do everything in their power to help the person before them in line kill Ragefire. That means that a bigger guild may actually help a smaller guild with their epic.<br>
<br>
5. They agree to do everything in their power to help the person after them in line kill Ragefire. That means going back to Skyfire IF POSSIBLE, with as many people that want to help. IF POSSIBLE means this, unless you are at a <br>
big raid, or a guild meeting, you should try to come. This should not happen all that often, considering there are already 2 people, and 2 guilds willing to help one another out.<br>
<br>
6. If cleric #1 is camping and goes linkdead, afk, or cannot find a sub to play his/her character, and Ragefire spawns, clric #2 who is next in line should inform cleric # 1's guild that Ragefire has spawned, and get them to mobilize. Cleric # 2 should also mobilize their own forces to help, and if cleric # 1 does not get back online quickly (let's say 30 minutes) and <br>
there is nobody that can log him on, person next in line has &quot;rights&quot; to that Ragefire spawn. Original person camping has all rights to the next spawn of Ragefire, the only thing that would change, is person next in line. Hence cleric # 1 would get bumped back a spot and cleric # 2 would get the <br>
current rage pop. This is done so that someone in zone doesn't KS Rage, or so that he doesn't despawn. (note): if #1 and #2 are not there, they both get bumped back a spot and # 3 takes the spawn and so on.<br>
<br>
7. Two people from the same guild cannot camp Ragefire back to back. This could be seen as spawn monopolizing, and we want to keep it fair. Also If you are unavailable for 2 Rage spawns back to back, you get booted to the end of the line. (this applies to only the #1,#2, and Possibly the #3 clerics, <br>
I would think).<br>
<br>
8. Each and everyone of the first 10 clerics on the list must /autojoin ragefire...If you do not do this and you miss something, you will only have yourself to blame. 10-20 on list should be in ragefire channel but it is not mandatory that they do this. This channel is for the clerics to discuss <br>
possible KS'ers and possible changes, and so on. <br>
<br>
9. Lastly, When cleric #1 is camping and cleric #2 needs to go afk, it is up to #2 to imform #1 that they are gonna be afk for extended periods of time, they have a guild meeting, they need to log for an hour or so, ect. It is soly up to #1 to agree or disagree with the time that #2 needs away...This <br>
also goes for #1 needing to leave and #2 will have to say if it is cool or not. Just remember to be nice and try to be understanding with each other, it is far better to help each other than to stab the other in the back. <br>
<br>
