<br>
Situation would work like this, you'd have 2 or 3 guilds in SolB trash talking each other and Zordak spawns.  One of the clerics runs up and spawns the dragon as claim to &quot;owning&quot; the spawned dragon.  Everyone beats down the dragon and the other cleric gets the experience on the kill, loots the heart, trash talks some more and gates out.  Now the cleric who did the hand in is screwed because he/she has to start over.  And VI's customer service doesn't subscribe to the &quot;Law of Common sense&quot; so they can't just look at the situation and re-imburse the lost items or the heart.<br>
<br>
Moving the spawn to Skyfire was just to remove Naggy from the bottleneck as an after thought.  Not every server has a group of eager UGoD Naggy killers that pretty much eliminate that part of the bottleneck.  Some other server guilds were having to level up twinks just to get Naggy out of the way.  It was not, however, the primary reason for the change in the quest.  <br>
<br>
Now VI has made it clear that they really don't want more than 2 cleric epics entering the world per week.  So the bottleneck stays, how do we make it more reasonable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>If I could fix it?</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
Triggered spawn where you get the hand in item back a la undead bard.  Zordak is a merchant, melees like Sirran, untargetable, perma-rooted, deathtouches, 1.2billion HP, and non-KOS.  Human doesn't respawn in 3 days after death guaranteed.  After those 3 days are up, there is a 12 hour spawn window.  So there is a reasonable camp time where you can get there in advance of and you never have to &quot;camp&quot; him for longer than 12 hours. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>If I want to screw the bottleneck, how about this?</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
Two Zordak's spawn, one in Naggy's lair and one in Skyfire.  The one in Skyfire spawns just like current.  The one in Naggy's lair spawns every 2 hours and becomes Ragefire when you hand him, I dunno, some random hard to get item.  Maybe a newly added Phara Dar scale?  This Ragefire spawns much higher level and is roughly an equal kill too, hrm, Yelniak?<br>
